description:
&lt;p&gt;We are pleased to announce this exciting opportunity for an AFC Band 6 post for the Mental Health Liaison Team (MHLT). The post holder will be working alongside the Clinical lead, supporting the delivery of service for the Mid Essex MHLT, ensuring that there are effective arrangements in place to meet service demand. The post holder will support the leadership team to ensure compliance with statutory duties; performance targets and quality improvement measures. The post holder will be expected to work as part of a 12 hours rota system (covering 24 hours 7 days per week).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be expected to provide a high quality, responsive service to meet the needs of individuals who are referred to the service. Focusing on working to the service specification and to achieve the performance targets set for the team. To work collaboratively, and in partnership with other clinicians within the acute hospitals, and specialist mental health services to ensure services provided are co-ordinated and focused on positive patient outcomes..&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Candidate should have at least 3 year experience at AFC Band 5, including experience in assessment and liaison work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A significant proportion of MHLT work is with Older age patients therefore experience in this field would be extremely beneficial.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Season Ticket Loans&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NHS discounts for staff&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent Training facilities and opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The opportunity to work bank shifts and expand knowledge and experience in other areas&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Salary Sacrifice schemes including lease cars and Cycle to Work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Buying and Selling annual leave scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameSam HagueJob titleClinical LeadEmail addresss.hague@nhs.netTelephone number01245 513706&lt;/p&gt;
